"{\"uid\": \"rnz.co.nz-news-olympics-2024-524573-olympics-2024-dame-lisa-carrington-claims-sixth-gold-medal-with-win-in-women-s-kayak-fours\", \"text\": \"The queen of kayaking has added another crown to her collection.  The country's most successful Olympian, Dame Lisa Carrington, has won a seventh medal and sixth gold, after spearheading the women's kayak four in their 500-metre final in Paris.  It was the first Olympic medal for the other three members of the crew, Alicia Hoskin, Olivia Brett and Tara Vaughan.  The win takes New Zealand's medal tally to 12.  The New Zealand crew celebrates after their win.Photo:AFP/OLIVIER MORIN  New Zealand powered out to first position at the start, but the German crew sneaked up on them approaching the 250m mark.  Germany then edged out in front to set up a thrilling finish.  Carrington's crew proved too quick however, getting to the line in one minute and 32 seconds.  After getting out of the water, the women hugged each other tightly in celebration.  The crew share a hug.Photo:AFP/OLIVIER MORIN  Speaking to Sky Sport, Brett said she was \\\"so proud\\\" of her boatmates.  \\\"That was an epic race and I am just so excited.\\\"  Vaughan said she was \\\"so grateful\\\" to the other three women.  \\\"Being a part of this team is absolutely the best.\\\"  Hoskin said the plan was to \\\"stay in our own boat\\\" and trust the strategy that had been put in place.  \\\"So proud, like it takes a lot of courage to do that. So we are really happy.\\\"  Carrington said the team, and everyone behind them, had put a lot of work into the Olympic campaign.  \\\"This is an incredibly special moment, especially to just be able to do it on our biggest stage, so yeah, it's surreal.  \\\"You just do not know when you line up. You never know what the results are going to be be. So it's amazing when you can come through, as we have.\\\"  Copyright \\u00a92024,Radio New Zealand  NZ cyclist Ellesse Andrews has won the women's keirin final comfortably, while Lisa Carrington's crew have claimed a win in the K4.  Dame Lisa Carrington is leading the charge in the kayaking, and the track cyclists are in rapid form.Audio  Aimee Fisher and Dame Lisa Carrington are on track for a gold medal showdown on Saturday.Audio  Aimee Fisher's major ambition is to win Olympic gold even if it means beating her hero.  The Alexandra kayaker won in a thrilling race and says he can not comprehend beating the world champion.  for ad-free news and current affairs  Olympics 2024 RSS  Follow RNZ News\"}"